      "raw_text": "At last there is some relief in\nsight for the people of North Di.\nvision street in the matter of the\nlong pending and much \"cussed''\nand discussed viaduct.\n\n\nID. c. Corbin, president of the Spo-\nkane International, last night an\nnounced to the city council, through\nCouncilman Jacob Schiller, that his\nline will enter the proposed new\nunion depot being financed by the\nNorth Coast and the Milwaukee.\n\n\nThe announcement was made\nthat the o. R. & N. will probably\ndo the stame thing and on Ns\nshowing action on the viaduct was\npostponed for the time being. The\ntracks leading to the proposed\nunion passenger station across Di.\nvision street will provide grade\nseparation."
